{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 3",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-596220892967862886 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/1wi06b-ei/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=596220892917269094&sectionId=596220892967862886)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyN_-3QOIM_text","label":"ggyN_-3QOIM_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:40px;\"><strong>Rescue Owner Exposes Hidden Truth: The 7-Day Timer That Killed Her German Shepherd</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggo5om_FqSk_text","label":"ggo5om_FqSk_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:30px;\"><strong>Rescue Owner Exposes Hidden Truth: The 7-Day Timer That Killed Her German Shepherd</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggdGn3gTUFc_text","label":"ggdGn3gTUFc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(51,51,51);font-size:16px;\"><i>November 05 2025 at 9:17 AM PST</i></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguJtS_za6C_text","label":"gguJtS_za6C_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(51,51,51);font-size:14px;\"><i>November 05 2025 at 9:17 AM PST</i></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggbePjQG512_text","label":"ggbePjQG512_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255,255,255,0);color:rgb(48,48,48);font-size:18px;\">I'm the one who kissed her goodbye that Tuesday morning, not knowing I'd never see her alive again</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggf0eVLYBd5_text","label":"ggf0eVLYBd5_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255,255,255,0);color:rgb(48,48,48);font-size:16px;\">I'm the one who kissed her goodbye that Tuesday morning, not knowing I'd never see her alive again</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6vXvdLMfJ_text","label":"gg6vXvdLMfJ_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">My name is Jennifer Martinez. Three weeks ago, those words destroyed my entire family.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">I'm the one who convinced my lonely parents to adopt Clove. I'm the one who set up their house. I'm the one who promised this rescue GSD would bring joy back to their retirement.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">If you read my Facebook post about losing Clove after just seven days, you know the basics. Now I'm sharing the horrifying truth I discovered that night—the hidden mechanism that's turning every meal into Russian roulette for millions of dogs.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Including yours.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg-9xXgvk1e_text","label":"gg-9xXgvk1e_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My name is Jennifer Martinez. Three weeks ago, those words destroyed my entire family.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I'm the one who convinced my lonely parents to adopt Clove. I'm the one who set up their house. I'm the one who promised this rescue GSD would bring joy back to their retirement.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">If you read my Facebook post about losing Clove after just seven days, you know the basics. Now I'm sharing the horrifying truth I discovered that night—the hidden mechanism that's turning every meal into Russian roulette for millions of dogs.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Including yours.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfiELU8bLY_text","label":"ggfiELU8bLY_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Daughter Who Thought She'd Done Everything Right</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggZgQkmlwKD_text","label":"ggZgQkmlwKD_text","default":"<p>For months, I'd been visiting our shelter, falling in love with this 4-year-old GSD named Clove.<br>Returned twice. \"Too energetic.\" \"Too needy.\"<br>But I saw what others missed—a soul desperate to be loved.<br>My parents had been drowning in retirement loneliness. Dad reading the same newspaper twice. Mom rearranging furniture for something to do.<br>\"What if you adopted Clove?\" I suggested.<br>Their faces transformed. First time I'd seen them truly smile in months.<br>I spent weeks preparing their house like a military operation:</p><ul><li>Fenced yard inspected for hazards</li><li>Stainless steel bowls (plastic causes bacteria)</li><li>Premium orthopedic bed in the sunroom</li><li>Every piece of dead wood cleared (choking hazard)</li></ul><p>The first six days were magical. My parents sent videos of Clove exploring, tail wagging, bringing life back to their silent house.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gghmVXbcamu_text","label":"gghmVXbcamu_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Daughter Who Thought She'd Done Everything Right</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpyQxXo9As_text","label":"ggpyQxXo9As_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">For months, I'd been visiting our shelter, falling in love with this 4-year-old GSD named Clove.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Returned twice. \"Too energetic.\" \"Too needy.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But I saw what others missed—a soul desperate to be loved.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My parents had been drowning in retirement loneliness. Dad reading the same newspaper twice. Mom rearranging furniture for something to do.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"What if you adopted Clove?\" I suggested.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Their faces transformed. First time I'd seen them truly smile in months.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I spent weeks preparing their house like a military operation:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Fenced yard inspected for hazards</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Stainless steel bowls (plastic causes bacteria)</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Premium orthopedic bed in the sunroom</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Every piece of dead wood cleared (choking hazard)</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The first six days were magical. My parents sent videos of Clove exploring, tail wagging, bringing life back to their silent house.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggD4lCia89b_text","label":"ggD4lCia89b_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">But when I visited to help with meals, I noticed something terrifying.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Clove inhaled food like she was being chased by death itself.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggCawNWuXmc_text","label":"ggCawNWuXmc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But when I visited to help with meals, I noticed something terrifying.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Clove inhaled food like she was being chased by death itself.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_9gIKZ-vf_text","label":"gg_9gIKZ-vf_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Warning Signs I Fatally Ignored</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGtzg3Q51p_text","label":"ggGtzg3Q51p_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Warning Signs I Fatally Ignored</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg1r-HTTm6Z_text","label":"gg1r-HTTm6Z_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Food anxiety from abandonment,\" the shelter explained. \"She wolfs it down in seconds.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>God, the irony of those words.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Tuesday morning, I left my parents' house at 7 AM for work.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I kissed Clove's head. \"See you tonight, beautiful girl. I'll bring those treats you love.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She wagged her tail and licked my hand.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>It was the last time I'd ever touch her warm fur.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw3dJki4cS_text","label":"ggw3dJki4cS_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Phone Call That Changed Everything</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpXrv6ypAK_text","label":"ggpXrv6ypAK_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">2:47 PM. Mom's name on my phone.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Her voice—I'd never heard that sound before. Pure terror mixed with grief.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Jennifer, you need to come home. Right now. It's Clove.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"What happened?!\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Your father found her by the back fence. She couldn't stand. Her stomach was... oh God, it's huge and hard like a drum. We're at the emergency vet but—\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"But WHAT, Mom?!\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"They said it's too late. Her stomach twisted. They want $4,800 for surgery but even then... only 60% chance. We applied for their emergency fund but got denied. Her condition's too advanced.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I collapsed in my office. My coworkers thought I was having a heart attack.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Don't let her die alone,\" I begged. \"I'm coming. I'm coming right now.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Honey, there's no time. She's suffering. We have to—\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>The sound my mother made next will haunt me until I die.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUvvGRqEtC_text","label":"ggUvvGRqEtC_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Food anxiety from abandonment,\" the shelter explained. \"She wolfs it down in seconds.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>God, the irony of those words.</strong></span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Tuesday morning, I left my parents' house at 7 AM for work.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">I kissed Clove's head. \"See you tonight, beautiful girl. I'll bring those treats you love.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She wagged her tail and licked my hand.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>It was the last time I'd ever touch her warm fur.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyNQz34guj_text","label":"ggyNQz34guj_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Phone Call That Changed Everything</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggq0jm5BPUy_text","label":"ggq0jm5BPUy_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">2:47 PM. Mom's name on my phone.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Her voice—I'd never heard that sound before. Pure terror mixed with grief.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Jennifer, you need to come home. Right now. It's Clove.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"What happened?!\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Your father found her by the back fence. She couldn't stand. Her stomach was... oh God, it's huge and hard like a drum. We're at the emergency vet but—\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"But WHAT, Mom?!\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"They said it's too late. Her stomach twisted. They want $4,800 for surgery but even then... only 60% chance. We applied for their emergency fund but got denied. Her condition's too advanced.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">I collapsed in my office. My coworkers thought I was having a heart attack.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Don't let her die alone,\" I begged. \"I'm coming. I'm coming right now.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Honey, there's no time. She's suffering. We have to—\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>The sound my mother made next will haunt me until I die.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3D0lPYhSg_text","label":"gg3D0lPYhSg_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Next Day's Desperate Search for Answers</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLe1Xm8zel_text","label":"ggLe1Xm8zel_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Next Day's Desperate Search for Answers</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggO40BEmS0G_text","label":"ggO40BEmS0G_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I couldn't sleep. Couldn't eat. Couldn't understand.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The next morning, I met Dr. Stevens, the emergency vet who'd tried to save Clove.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Bloat happens when dogs swallow massive amounts of air while eating,\" she explained.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"But I tried slowing her down!\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Those methods help with speed but don't address the real cause.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She revealed something that changed everything:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Fast eating is actually a neurological trigger from survival instincts.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"What?!\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She pulled up Clove's X-rays. The entire stomach cavity was black.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBZtk9HT9C_text","label":"ggBZtk9HT9C_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">I couldn't sleep. Couldn't eat. Couldn't understand.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">The next morning, I met Dr. Stevens, the emergency vet who'd tried to save Clove.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Bloat happens when dogs swallow massive amounts of air while eating,\" she explained.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"But I tried slowing her down!\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Those methods help with speed but don't address the real cause.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She revealed something that changed everything:</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>\"Fast eating is actually a neurological trigger from survival instincts.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"What?!\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She pulled up Clove's X-rays. The entire stomach cavity was black.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggI-9VyoLjU_text","label":"ggI-9VyoLjU_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"See all that darkness?<strong> That's air. Every 'fast' meal, Clove was swallowing massive amounts of air along with food.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Speed isn't the problem. The problem is WHY dogs gulp.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She showed me brain scans that changed everything.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"When dogs see food—ANY amount in ANY formation—their amygdala fires like they're under attack. Their brain literally cannot distinguish between eating peacefully at home and<strong> fighting a wolf pack for the last scrap of meat.</strong>\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoKytRoRSm_text","label":"ggoKytRoRSm_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Study That Should Be Criminal to Hide</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsLsOgwr0P_text","label":"ggsLsOgwr0P_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"See all that darkness? <strong>That's air. Every 'fast' meal, Clove was swallowing massive amounts of air along with food.</strong>\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>\"Speed isn't the problem. The problem is WHY dogs gulp.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She showed me brain scans that changed everything.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"When dogs see food—ANY amount in ANY formation—their amygdala fires like they're under attack. Their brain literally cannot distinguish between eating peacefully at home and <strong>fighting a wolf pack for the last scrap of meat.</strong>\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggFcLqj8SkA_text","label":"ggFcLqj8SkA_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Study That Should Be Criminal to Hide</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3Ojny5vma_text","label":"gg3Ojny5vma_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Dr. Stevens pulled up research that made me physically sick:</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>\"Traditional slow feeders reduce eating speed by 40% but air intake by only 10%.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"ARE YOU KIDDING ME?!\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Every traditional ‘'slow feeder'. The dogs still see a pile to defend. They work harder to gulp but they STILL GULP. We see bloat cases using slow feeders every single night.\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Then why does everyone recommend—\"</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"Because a $5 tennis ball is easier to sell than the truth. Because most vets learned outdated information. Because by the time dogs get to emergency...\"&nbsp;</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She gestured at the room where Clove died.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">\"We see the failures. We know what doesn't work. But nobody listens to emergency vets until it's too late.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4nutx1fds_text","label":"gg4nutx1fds_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Solution Emergency Vets Hide From Regular Vets</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggIiXTyF0h7_text","label":"ggIiXTyF0h7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>\"There IS something that works,\" </strong>Dr. Stevens said.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">She showed me a video that made my hands shake with rage.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoKAkDjSd4_text","label":"ggoKAkDjSd4_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Dr. Stevens pulled up research that made me physically sick:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Traditional slow feeders reduce eating speed by 40% but air intake by only 10%.\"</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"ARE YOU KIDDING ME?!\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Every traditional ‘'slow feeder'. The dogs still see a pile to defend. They work harder to gulp but they STILL GULP. We see bloat cases using slow feeders every single night.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Then why does everyone recommend—\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Because a $5 tennis ball is easier to sell than the truth. Because most vets learned outdated information. Because by the time dogs get to emergency...\"&nbsp;</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She gestured at the room where Clove died.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"We see the failures. We know what doesn't work. But nobody listens to emergency vets until it's too late.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gglxtKKCNAy_text","label":"gglxtKKCNAy_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Solution Emergency Vets Hide From Regular Vets</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPslHpDfS7_text","label":"ggPslHpDfS7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"There IS something that works,\"</strong> Dr. Stevens said.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She showed me a video that made my hands shake with rage.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9nMD4GEmA_text","label":"gg9nMD4GEmA_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">A Shepherd —identical to Clove—eating from something called a CalmBowl. But instead of the frantic gulping that killed my parents' dog, this one was... peaceful.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"The rotating blade barrier system doesn't just slow eating. It <strong>completely deactivates the neurological trigger.</strong>\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"How is that possible?\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"The circular blade channels create three-dimensional barriers that make scooping and gulping physically impossible. Instead of triggering competition panic, it activates natural foraging behavior—like searching for food in nature.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggtqUxy93e2_text","label":"ggtqUxy93e2_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Massacre Happening In Your Kitchen Right Now</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOSIqzVfRs_text","label":"ggOSIqzVfRs_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Dr. Stevens showed me last month's statistics from just her clinic:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">8 dogs admitted with bloat</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">6 died despite surgery</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Average time from eating to death: 47 minutes</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Every. Fucking. Night,\" she said, tears in her eyes. \"I watch dogs die while owners sob about the slow feeder that 'worked great until tonight.'\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Shepherds are the second highest risk breed. Deep chest cavity. More room for the stomach to flip. <strong>Your parents' dog was a ticking time bomb from the first meal.</strong>\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8gTTM9s_w_text","label":"gg8gTTM9s_w_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Special Solution That Actually Works</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggU-GwWiA-7_text","label":"ggU-GwWiA-7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The CalmBowl's rotating blade barrier system isn't marketing bullshit:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Circular blade</strong> channels make scooping physically impossible</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Triggers natural foraging instinct</strong> instead of competition panic</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Slows eating 15x</strong> from 30 seconds to 8+ minutes eliminating gulping reflex</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Works for all snout shapes</strong> from pugs to collies</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Medical-grade stainless steel</strong> (plastic grows deadly bacteria)</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Approved by veterinarians</strong> who see bloat deaths nightly</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Zero cases in many years of tracking.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNL5VTPt6l_text","label":"ggNL5VTPt6l_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Parents Who Almost Shared Our Nightmare</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggloYarTIIr_text","label":"ggloYarTIIr_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Lost my first Shepherd in my arms to bloat. $6,000 surgery failed. When I got another, the emergency vet MANDATED CalmBowl. Said 'I'm not watching you go through that again.' Three years, zero scares. I actually sleep at night.\" - Patricia K., Denver</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Watched my neighbor's dog die from bloat IN THEIR DRIVEWAY. Couldn't make the 8-minute drive. Bought CalmBowl that night. The difference is insane—from violent gulping to actual chewing. My GSD is 7 now.\" - Michael S., Dallas &nbsp;</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"I'm an ER vet tech. The bloat deaths I see... it's always 'but we had a slow feeder!' EVERY staff member here uses CalmBowl. It's the ONLY thing that addresses the real cause.\" - Dr. Amanda R., Phoenix</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBTEO3jrHK_text","label":"ggBTEO3jrHK_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The 30-Minute Timer Is Already Ticking</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggXneSbzlAz_text","label":"ggXneSbzlAz_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Right now, your dog is either protected or playing Russian roulette.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Those air bubbles don't disappear. They accumulate. Waiting.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">One jump. One roll. One playful moment after dinner.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Then you have 30 minutes and a $5,000 decision.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The CalmBowl costs less than 1% of emergency surgery. Less than Clove's cremation. Less than the therapy my parents need.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwfxZItSYc_text","label":"ggwfxZItSYc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Infinitely less than knowing you could have prevented it.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Waggier makes only 100 per month due to precision manufacturing. They're offering<strong> 35% off </strong>because the founder lost his own GSD to bloat—just like Clove.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggk6fEZeoPc_text","label":"ggk6fEZeoPc_text","default":"<p><a href=\"https://waggier.com/products/waggier-calmbowl\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#324FE8;font-size:16px;\"><strong><u>Click the button below now to check if Waggier CalmBowl is still available with the special discount!</u></strong></span></a></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBWEHPkZ7E_text","label":"ggBWEHPkZ7E_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Don't Let Your Parents Bury Their Best Friend</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggWxch0o9E7_text","label":"ggWxch0o9E7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I wasn't there when Clove died. I was 40 minutes away in an office, thinking I'd see her that evening.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My parents held her as she took her last breath. They haven't recovered.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Seven days. That's all we got because I didn't know the difference between slowing eating and stopping air gulping.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Now you do.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Your dog is depending on you knowing what I didn't.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Don't become the next family in Dr. Stevens' death statistics</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggc3ZtL1ibO_text","label":"ggc3ZtL1ibO_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Just Want to Share</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUGokFJlWW_text","label":"ggUGokFJlWW_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I'm not trying to scare anyone. But if your dog inhales their food, please understand—<strong>every meal could trigger bloat that gives you just 30 minutes to save them.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">After losing Clove, I've become obsessed with warning other dog parents. Maybe too obsessed. But last week when my coworker mentioned her Lab \"wolfs down dinner,\" I nearly cried.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I showed her everything Dr. Stevens taught me about the neurological trigger. How tennis balls and maze bowls don't stop the deadly air gulping.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>She got a CalmBowl. Two days later she texted: \"He's actually CHEWING. First time in 3 years.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>That's why I'm sharing this</strong>. Not because I'm selling anything. Because somewhere tonight, another family is watching their dog gulp dinner, not knowing they're 30 minutes from disaster.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8uKrvdrn__text","label":"gg8uKrvdrn__text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Covered by a 90-Day Money Back Guarantee</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggWU0mwVWh3_text","label":"ggWU0mwVWh